Thought we were done with hiring? 🤔

We’re back with a new opportunity for you 🫵 to join the UDesign team. This time, we’re looking for 2 project managers! 💼

Specializing in creative and/or product design, you’ll be directing our project and design teams with experiences to…

💡 Develop your leadership and design capabilities
💡 Network with creatives and designers within the GTA
💡 Manage complex, but rewarding projects

Ready to lead our designers with creativity and passion? Apply now! 🚀

⏰ Applications close September 7th at 6:00pm.
🔗 Visit the link in our bio for the application link!

#udesign #graphic #graphicdesign #projectmanager #design #figma #art #creative #productdesign #creativedesign #uoft #utsg #utm #utsc

💥 IT’S VERY DEMURE TO VISIT UDESIGN AT UTSU CLUB FAIR 💥 

Ready to make your design mark on campus? Want to join a tight-knitted community of creatives just like yourself? Say less, UDesign x UTSU Club Fair is where you’re meant to be! 🌟 🫧   

Come say hi, learn more about what we do, and, most importantly, be a part of something special! See you there!   

📍 UTSG’s Front Campus  
🗓️ August 30th, from 1:00-4:00PM.   
🔗 Too much hassle? UDesign is hiring, visit the link in our bio to join the team!

Triple en Genre just got womanized! 

On Friday, August 30th at 8:30pm at SoCap Comedy, Emily Paterson and Clare Mooney will be hosting the first ever all female edition of the show!

Closing the show with an improvised Rom-Com we have Bita Joudaki, Blair MacMillan, Carley Thorne, Emily Paterson, and Clare Mooney!

Opening the show will be Sinthea Chowdry, Noor Dhanda, Julia Ettlinger, Emily Ferrier, and Meredith Mullen! They’ll be putting a spin on a “Modern Fantasy” (ex. A Cinderella Story, The Princess Diaries, or Aquamarine)

In the second set we have Erika Dowd, Chrissie Gross, Amrutha Krishnan, Janet Mac, Karley Saagi, and Emma DeCorte. They’ll be doing an improvised Coming-Of-Age film!

Tickets available for $15 at:

engenre.eventbrite.ca (link in bio)

See you on 8/30 at 8:30!!!!

Triple En-Genre takes on your fave Reality TV genres this Friday, 10pm, at @socapcomedy!

We’ve got Saba Akhtar, Katie Chin, Dan Jeon, Logan Midroni, JP Pathmanthan, and a mystery guest improvising the DATING SHOW you’ve been waiting for!

We’ve got Josh Bricker, Ren David-Dimen, Lily Lai, Ana Luiza Valente, Victor Paisley, and Ian Yamamoto improvising the SURVIVOR GAME-SHOW you’ve been waiting for!

And finally we’ve got Chris Mundy, Lance Oribello, Asha Vijayasingham and Josh Zimmerman improvising the HOME RENOVATION show you’ve been waiting for!

This is prime time television, so don’t miss it!

Tickets are at engenre.eventbrite.ca

This Friday is the ONE YEAR ANNIVERSARY of Triple En-Genre 🥳🥳!! Aug 9, 8:30pm on the 3rd floor of @socapcomedy !

It’s gonna be a very fun show with some celebratory festivities! Plus we’ll be hanging out post show for some more celebrations!

I’m super pumped to have this awesome cast to commemorate this special occasion: 

Opening the show it’s Brandon Craggs, Nick Blanchard, Taelor Lewis-Joseph, Clare Mooney, Rhys Naylor and Emily Paterson! They’ll be doing an improvised Murder Mystery!

Up second it’s Kristi Boulton, Kyle Claeys, Lance Oribello, Griffin Toplitsky, Ian Yamamoto, Kitty Zhang and a mystery guest! They’ll be doing an improvised historical romance (like Bridgerton)!

Coming up third it’s Nitin Anand, MJ Asuza, Sinthea Chowdhury, Tinny Nguyen, Austin Sherman, and Adam Stockley! They’ll be doing an improvised Medical Drama. 

Closing the show it’s Shaun Hunter, Devon Hyland, Bita Joudaki, Matt McCready, and myself! We’ll be bringing back the improvised Sitcom, which hasn’t been done at a Triple En-Genre since the very first show!

You can get FREE (or PWYC) tickets at engenreanniversary.eventbrite.ca

Hope to see you there!!

Triple En-Genre is turning 1 year old! Come celebrate with us this Friday, 8:30pm at SoCap (3rd floor)! We’ve got an extra special show and some fun celebration festivities!

Tickets are PWYC at engenreanniversary.eventbrite.ca (if you’re interested in coming please sign up on the eventbrite so we have an idea of numbers!). 

Featuring: Nitin Anand, MJ Asuza, Tyra Banda, Nick Blanchard, Sinthea Chowdhury, Kyle Claeys, Shaun Hunter, Bita Joudaki, Taelor Lewis-Joseph, Matt McCready, Clare Mooney, Tinny Nguyen, Lance Oribello, Emily Paterson, Adam Stockley, Austin Sherman, Griffin Toplitsky, Ian Yamamoto, Josh Zimmerman, and more TBA guests!

Hope to see you there!
